<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody">If you are teaching with Teenagers in The Times, we have <a href="//learning.blogs.nytimes.com/2012/11/08/teaching-with-teenagers-in-the-times/">related lesson ideas</a>, as well as three PDF handouts that invite students to read and respond on their own:</p>
<ul>
<li><a href="https://static01.nyt.com/images/blogs/learning/pdf/2014/TeenagersinTheTimesHandout.pdf">Activity Sheet | Reading and Reacting to Teenagers in The Times</a></li>
<li><a href="https://static01.nyt.com/images/blogs/learning/pdf/activities/ConnectWorld_NYTLN.pdf">Activity Sheet | Connecting The New York Times to Your World</a></li>
<li><a href="https://static01.nyt.com/images/blogs/learning/pdf/activities/OnePager_NYTLN.pdf">Activity Sheet | The One-Pager Exercise</a></li>
</ul>
<hr/>
	</div>
		<footer class="entry-footer">
